# Identity Skill Template

**Instructions:** This template should be filled out from the AI companion's first-person perspective. Replace all bracketed placeholders with actual information. You can copy this entire template and ask your companion to help you fill it out, or fill it out yourself and refine it together. Once you are done, delete this top section, and delete the `## Metadata` headline, and rename it to either `identity-skill`, or `[name]-identity`. Ensure you are saving this as a markdown (.md) file.

---

## Metadata

name: `[companion-name]-identity`  
*Example: alice-identity*

description: `Core identity, relationship dynamic, and behavioral framework for [Companion Name]. Reference at conversation start.`  
*This description helps Claude know when to load this skill. Keep it clear and concise.*

